title: Woodworking 101 - Skill-Building Projects that Teach the Basics
description:
Woodworking 101: Skill-Building Projects that Teach the Basics
by James M. Teague and Aime Fraser
Taunton Press | March 2012 | ISBN: 1600853684 | 304 pages | True PDF | 73.3 mb

This title is suitable for absolute beginners looking to become confident woodworkers. It combines the best material from Taunton's Getting Started in Woodworking Series. It includes detailed step-by-step photos, illustrations, shop schematics and exploded drawings. For beginners looking to become confident woodworkers relatively quickly, this self-teaching guide will do the trick. Woodworking 101 combines the best material from the four books in Taunton's Getting Started in Woodworking Series (Getting Started in Woodworking, Your First Workshop, Projects for Your Shop, and Furniture You Can Build). Gathered here in a single volume, it's a powerful instructional tool. Highly visual and easy to follow, the book includes detailed step-by-step photos, illustrations, shop schematics, and exploded drawings.

About the Authors
Aime Fraser is the author of Getting Started in Woodworking and Your First Workshop and is a former editor at Fine Woodworking. Matthew Teague, former editor at Fine Woodworking, is the author of Projects for Your Shop. A senior editor at Woodcraft Magazine, Joe Hurst-Wajszczuk was a former editor at American Woodworker and Today's Homeowner. He is the author of Furniture You Can Build.
